MADE BY: Ripudaman Singh Sidhu
How to make wine at home:
1. Buy brewers yeast
2. Buy Good quality grapes of your choice.
3. Wash the grapes properly
4. Sterlize the container/vessel and all the tools you will be using for fermentation
5. Wash your hands.
6. Mash the grapes
7. Add the yeast
8. Seal the container and make a vent to release the pressure buildup
9. place it in a dark place for the fermentation to take place
10. after 1 month, seperate the liquid from the grape mash and pour it into a dark glass bottle
11. let it sit for 15-20 days without disturbing.
12. Enjoy the wine.
